## M20a.2 negative: bare untyped `self` in first position.
##
## Per GPT-5.5's pre-commit review: once `self` is special enough to
## power receiver-mode metadata, it must not silently become an
## associated/static method's untyped first param. Users wanting a
## by-value receiver must spell it: `self: Self` (or `self: User`).
## Bare-`self` sugar for by-value receivers is deliberately deferred.
##
## EXPECTED: sema error: `self` parameter requires an explicit receiver type.

struct User
  name: String

  fun greet(self) -> String
    "hi"

sub main()
  u = User(name: "Steve")
  print(u.greet())
